defaultSRdefault3default: Make local spenddefault, improving the environmentdefault and local employment (including the use of SME’s) compulsory in Local Government through introducing contract commitments on every procurement exercise.default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
defaultThe simple answer to this is no – reference the ‘Key Benefits’ of using Scape (above).  Local Government uses 3 main methods of procurement:
defaultScape procurement arrangements are always collaborative in nature and save local authorities 14% on average compared with traditionally tendering.  So why aren’t all LA’s making best use of these arrangements?  See recommendation SR1 on page 3.
default&#xa0;
defaultPFI in principle looks a really good procurement option but the way the PFI have been procured to date has meant the focus of the procurement has moved away from delivery of a contract, building, service or function to how to leverage risk onto the successful PFI partner.  This is exactly the opposite how Scape procure; PFI is complex, Scape makes it simple; PFI is time consuming, Scape is quick; and finally PFI is in the majority of cases  unaffordable, Scape gives financial certainty.  However, private finance is essential to how local government procurement is funded in the future.  PFI is broken so what’s the solution?
default&#xa0;
defaultSRdefault4default:default PFI needs to be scrapped and a new vehicle to access private finance made available that’s defaultsimple, quick and certain. default&#xa0;
